Package com.eddy.docker.api

Interface Docker

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultDocker
    public interface Docker
    This interface defines the API that abstracts client access to the DefaultDocker API through DockerClient. It provides all the necessary commands required for running sandbox docker programs. It can be used as-is, but it is recommended to use the API wrapper DockerSandbox which abstracts any setup and execution steps that this class requires. The DockerSandbox is the most stable means of using this API since any changes (particularly breaking changes) made here would be automatically made to the DockerSandbox class, meaning that any existing methods (i.e. not new ones) your code is using will compile and still run as documented even if the Docker API has changed in the background
    Since:
    0.5.0

      • copyTarToContainer

        void copyTarToContainer​(java.lang.String containerId,
                        java.lang.String remotePath,
                        java.io.FileInputStream tarStream)
        Copies the provided tar to the remote path on the specified container
        Parameters:
        containerId - the id of the container
        remotePath - the path to the directory the tar should be extracted on
        tarStream - the input stream to the tar. This is not a TarArchiveInputStream since tar decompression is done by DockerClient

      • createContainer

        java.lang.String createContainer​(java.lang.String profileName,
                                 Docker.Command command,
                                 Docker.Bindings bindings,
                                 WorkingDirectory workingDirectory,
                                 java.lang.String stdin,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> envs)
        Create a container and retrieve the ID of the created container. Warning: if using stdin, you have to ensure that the command will in fact use stdin or else the call to getResult will return a Result with Result.isTimedOut() returning true
        Parameters:
        profileName - the name of the profile to look up. If a profile cannot be found, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown
        command - the command to run on the container
        bindings - any bindings for the container
        workingDirectory - the working directory for the container to work with
        stdin - the stdin input as a String. If Stdin is not required, pass in null or ""
        envs - environment variables to be set inside the docker container
        Returns:
        the ID of the created container

      • cleanupContainers

        void cleanupContainers()
        This method removes any containers that were running and were started by this class. This should be called if an exception occurred that may result in docker containers not being removed correctly which may result in conflict name errors.
